==English==
===Etymology===
Anglo-Latin ''[[francalanus]]'', from ''[[francalis]]'' ‘held without fees’, from ''[[francus]]'' ‘fee’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈfræŋklɪn/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{italbrac|obsolete except historical}} A [[freeholder]], especially as belonging to a class of [[landowners]] in the 14th and 15th century ranking below the [[gentry]].

